<li>
<a name="fn1_ref"></a>
        <span class="xref big">1</span>
        <div>Since the qualified threshold in the Chamber of Deputies is 3/5 of the members (or 308 votes), the LPI for the approval of a ‘PEC’ ranges from 0 (0/308) to a maximum of 1.66 (513/308), rounded to 1.7. In this study, we consider only nominal roll-call votes requiring a qualified threshold in cases of approval – that is, cases in which a majority of 308 votes is necessary. Rejection bills are fewer in number and fall outside the scope of this analysis.</div>
      </li>
<li>
<a name="fn2_ref"></a>
